results.name: Triangle T(n,f): the number of signed cubic graphs on 2n vertices with f edges of the first sign.
comment: These are connected, undirected, simple cubic graphs where each edge is signed as either "+" or "-". Row n has 1+3n entries, 0<=f<=3n. The column f=0 (1, 0, 1, 2, 5,...) counts the cubic graphs (A002851). The column f=1 (0, 1, 3, 14, 91, 706,...) counts the edge-rooted cubic graphs.
xref: Cf. A002851 (first column), A321304 (signed vertices), A302939 (signed trees).
results.author: _R. J. Mathar_, Nov 03 2018
